[assistant] Fixed the stale patch extraction issue.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `extractJavaXmlPatch` had already produced only the `javax/xml/parsers` classes before the `javax/xml/transform` include was added.
[assistant] - Gradle considered the existing `Copy` task output up-to-date, so `javax/xml/transform/SecuritySupport.class` was never copied into the patch directory.
[assistant] - As a result, `--patch-module` could not expose `javax.xml.transform.SecuritySupport`, causing `ClassNotFoundException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Updated `extractJavaXmlPatch` from `Copy` to `Sync` in:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/build.gradle`
[assistant] 
[assistant] This makes the generated patch directory synchronized with the configured include set and should cause the task to refresh correctly.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Amended commit:
[assistant] - `3fe29ec01 Cover xmlParserAPIs transform SecuritySupport resources`
[assistant] 
